The '''Naqsh-e Jahan derby''' is a [[football (soccer)|football]] match played annually in of [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]], between the two rival professional teams of the city: [[Zob Ahan F.C.]] and [[Sepahan F.C.]]. [[Naqsh-e Jahan]] is an important square in old centrum of [[Isfahan]].
This match is also called as '''Isfahan derby'''.
According to Iranian football journalist Afshin Afshar, the competition is one of the most popular annual football events in Iran.<ref>[http://www.lastkick.com/?p=4301 Lastkick.com]</ref>
==History== Esfahan derby goes back to the 1970s, when [[Zob Ahan F.C.]] and [[Sepahan F.C.]] faced each other in [[Takht Jamshid Cup]] seasons([[Takht Jamshid Cup 1974%E2%80%9375|1974/75]], [[Takht Jamshid Cup 1975%E2%80%9376|1975/76]], [[Takht Jamshid Cup 1976%E2%80%9377|1976/77]], [[Takht Jamshid Cup 1977%E2%80%9378|1977/78]]). Their rivalry resumed in the 1990s when they faced each other in [[Azadegan League]] seasons ([[Azadegan League 1993%E2%80%9394|1993/94]], [[Azadegan League 1996%E2%80%9397|1996/97]], [[Azadegan League 1997%E2%80%9398|1997/98]]) and from then on the two met each other twice a year.
